# Screenshot tag-team

- **Roles**: The human sets zoom and scroll position; the agent captures screenshots only when told to.
- **Open**: Agent may navigate to the target URL once (e.g. preview route). Human adjusts zoom afterward if needed.
- **First shot (top)**: Human zooms out and scrolls to the **top**, then says **ready**. Agent takes **one** screenshot **without** navigating or reloading.
- **Second shot (bottom)**: Human scrolls to the **bottom**, then says **ready**. Agent takes **one** screenshot **without** navigating or reloading.
- **Stability**: After human says ready, agent must not refresh, navigate, resize viewport, or change zoom—only capture.
- **Clarity**: If capture fails or state is wrong, agent asks human to fix zoom/scroll and say ready again; agent does not improvise extra steps.
